otal value of life insurance policies issued in  the metropolitan life insurance company tower was commissioned to serve as metlife’s rd street headquarters in lower manhattan completed two years later the building was the worlds tallest until  and remained the companys headquarters until  for many years an illustration of the building with light emanating from the tip of its spire and the slogan the light that never fails featured prominently in metlife’s advertising by  metlife insured every fifth man woman and child in the united states and canada during the s it also began to diversify its portfolio by reducing the percentage of individual mortgages in favor of public utility bonds investments in government securities and loans for commercial real estate the company financed the construction of the empire state building in  as well as provided capital to build rockefeller center in  during world war ii metlife placed more than  percent of its total assets in war bonds and was the largest single private contributor to the allied cause postwaredit company president leroy lincoln in  metropolitan life logo ca  during the postwar era the company expanded its suburban presence decentralized operations and refocused its career agency system to serve all market segments it also began to market group insurance products to employers and institutions by  operations were segmented into four primary businesses group insurance personal insurance pensions and investments in  metlife purchased what became known as the metlife building for  million from a group that included pan american world airways metlife building at  park ave in new york city the building is no longer owned by metlife demutualization and ipoedit in  metlife converted from a mutual insurance company operated for the benefit of its policyholders to a forprofit public company the demutualization process allowed metlife to enter unrelated insurance businesses and increase executive compensation policyholders received some stock in the new company in this process metlife was accused of breaching federal securities laws by misrepresenting and omitting information in materials given to policyholders during this process resulting in years of litigation ending with a  million settlement in  acquisitions sales and major dealsedit   merged with united mutual life insurance company the only africanamerican life insurer in new york in     acquired executive lifes single premium deferred annuity business which was worth approximately  billion metlife also acquired the firms life insurance business valued at about  million   purchased new england mutual life insurance company   acquired security first group in  for  million   acquired lincoln national corporations individual disability income unit   bought out reinsurance provider genamerica corporation for  billion as well as its subsidiaries reinsurance group of america and conning corporation that year the company had grown to serve  million policyholders   demutualization and ipo the initial public offering was valued at  billion which was the largest ipo to that date in united states financial history metlife policyholders were asked to choose a cash or stock stake this ipo made metlife the most widely owned stock in the united states and it raised metlifes value to over  billion by  metlifes reported number of policyholders had risen to  million and that year it had become the united states number one life insurer surpassing prudential according to the new york times    million voice and data network management deal with att solutions   acquired grand bank of kingston new jersey which was renamed metlife bank   invested  billion in the united states stock market during  immediately after the september th terrorist attacks   acquired citigroup’s travelers life  annuity and all of citigroup’s international insurance businesses for  billion at the time of the deal which was completed on july   the travelers acquisition made metl